title: Angular and energy distribution of photoneutrons.

x4freetext: Angular and energy distribution of photoneutrons.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Voprosy Teoreticheskoy i Yadernoy Fiziki, Issue.1, p.75 (1968)

x4freetext: Article is not available.
All data from A.I.Lepestkin.
Collection of recoiled protons.
400 mum thick NIKFI IA-2 emulsions of
5*3 cm**2 size.
Energy spectra were corrected for:
a) the variation of nuclear emulsion thickness;
b) the dependence of the n-p cross section on
neutron energy;
c) the probability that proton tracks end outside
the emulsion;
d) the background.
Statistical errors of measurement.
The mean uncertainty of the measurements of
the angles.
Energy distributions of photoneutrons from bismuth,
gold and tantalum for the angles from 30 to 150 degr.
at 19 MeV bremsstrahlung end-point energy were
measured. The part of the `direct` neutrons for each
spectrum was found. Angular distributions of
photoneutrons from bismuth for 14 and 19 MeV values
of upper limit of bremsstrahlung spectrum were
obtained.
By A.I.Lepestkin.
.Data were compiled in SCJAD of Saratov
State University.
Corrected by V.Varlamov, V.Mclane
Corrected by SD and VV: REFERENCE, METHOD,
PART-DET, SAMPLE, REACTION, STATUS, DATA, new date
format, lowercase.
